# {{ component.name|titleize }} Theme

The **{{ component.name|titleize }}** Theme is for [Grav CMS](https://github.com/getgrav/grav). This README.md file should be modified to describe the features, installation, configuration, and general usage of this theme.

## Description

{{ component.description }}

This theme is built with [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) and the [daisyUI](https://daisyui.com/) component library, with [Alpine.js](https://alpinejs.dev/) for interactivity.

## Building the CSS

Install the toolchain and compile Tailwind + daisyUI:

```
npm install
```

Then, from the theme folder:

- `npm run build` — compile once (development)
- `npm run watch` — recompile on change (development)
- `npm run prod` — minified production build

The compiled stylesheet is written to `dist/css/site.css`. When you are ready to ship, run `npm run prod` and turn on **Production Mode** in the theme configuration.

## Theming

daisyUI ships light and dark themes out of the box. Pick one in the theme configuration (`daisyUI Theme`); it is applied via the `data-theme` attribute on the `<html>` element. Add more themes in `tailwind.config.js`.
